Using getArrivalsDeparturesDbIterator() reads in only data as needed so good with respect to memory usage but it does a separate query for each row. Reading in list of all data is quick but can cause memory problems if reading in a very large amount of data. This method is a good compromise because it only reads in a batch of data at a time so is not as memory intensive yet it is quite fast. With a batch size of 50k found it to run in under 1/4 the time as with the iterator method.
